  "text": "For western blotting, cells were lysed with a buffer containing 50 mM Tris-HCl (pH 7.5), 250 mM NaCl, 3 mM EDTA, 3 mM EGTA, 1% (v/v) Triton X-100, 0.5% IGEPAL CA-630, 10% (v/ v) glycerol, 1 mM phenylmethylsulfonyl fluoride, 2 mg/ml pepastatin, 10 mM E64, 2 mM NaF, 1 mM Na 3 VO 4 and 1 mM microcystin. SDS-PAGE and blotting were carried out using standard procedures. Antibodies raised against the following proteins were used: actin (A2103; Sigma-Aldrich), cyclin E (HE12; Cell Signaling), GAPDH (GAPDH-71.1; Sigma-Aldrich), hspB1, (ADI-SPA-801; Enzo), p21 waf1 (F5; Santa Cruz Biotechnology), p27 kip1 (C-19; Santa Cruz Biotechnology), poly (ADPribose) polymerase (PARP)1 (9542; Cell Signaling), proliferating cell nuclear antigen (PCNA) (PC10; Santa Cruz Biotechnology), and a-tubulin (DM1A; Sigma-Aldrich). RNA was isolated using RNeasy kit (Qiagen) and cDNA was synthesized using the High Capacity cDNA Reverse Transcription Kit (Applied Biosystems). mRNAs were quantified by qRT-PCR using Taqman Gene expression assays and data analysed by relative quantitation (with standard curves) with normalisation to GAPDH mRNA as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
